    <note>Xue(1) Yi [7109] His ancestors were Hedong jun Xue(1). Tian's [808] son. In order of marriages: Tang(2) Su's [1600] son-in-law, Liu(2) Zong's [1240] grandson-in-law, Li(2) Jianzhong's [3483] grandson-in-law, and Chen(1) Zongyuan's [3090] son-in-law. Li(2) Jianzhong came from a family which had moved from Jingzhao to Sichuan at the end of the Tang. Chen(1) Zongyuan was a Xinghua, Xianyou resident, whose father and uncle held office during the early years of Song. Zongyuan's grandfather, Chen(1) Hongjin [3067], was a general under Min, then was made governor of southern Fujian by Li(2) Yu(5) [3551], last ruler of the Southern Tang, and came to court to present the territory of Zhangzhou and Quanzhou to Song during the reign of Zhao(1) Taizong [9002]. Xue(1) Yi's son-in-law, Zhang(1) Xu [3146], was Zhang(1) Kui's [250] nephew and Zhang(1) Dao's [298] cousin. Han Qi, WJ, 47.15b; Sima Guang, WJ, 79.1a-4a.</note>
